    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Sumter So. Ca.</placeName>
                <date>May 13th/58</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Knowing your ability to<lb/> diffuse lights on a subject that I
                am<lb/> comparatively ignorant of, and believing<lb/> in your perfect willingness to
                aid the<lb/> benighted. I propose asking you a<lb/> few questions on the subject of
                our<lb/> religion. I unfortunately have been <lb/>very imperfectly instructed
                myself<lb/> &amp; living as I do out of a congregation<lb/> have no means of
                instructing my<lb/> children; I have a son a youth of<lb/> 17, whose mind is very
                mature<lb/> circumstances have induced him<lb/> to open a correspondence with
                me<lb/> on the subject of religion &amp; he pro<lb/> pounds the following questions
                to me.</p>
            <p>1 Why are you a Jew?</p>
            <p>2 What are the fundamental grounds<lb/> of the Jewish belief? 3 What are<lb/> your
                ideas of a saviour? 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> What<lb/> is your belief in regard to
                salvation<lb/> &amp; damnation? 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Do you believe in<lb/> the
                divinity of the Bible, or do you<lb/> think it an allegory? These he says</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>are a few questions he would like me<lb/> to answer, as he is ignorant of his<lb/>
                creed he desires <hi rend="underline">reasons</hi> for his<lb/> faith &amp; objects
                to taking his belief<lb/> from another. My son is at present<lb/> in
                    <placeName>Washington City</placeName> but proposes<lb/> visiting my sister
                    <persName>Mrs. G. C. Levy</persName> next<lb/> month. I propose answering
                his<lb/> queries as soon as I get <hi rend="underline">your</hi> answers<lb/> &amp;
                would be very much obliged<lb/> if you would direct my atten<lb/>tion to such books
                as contain<lb/> the <hi rend="underline">strongest</hi> arguments in support<lb/> of
                our faith that I may not only<lb/> be able to instruct him but <hi rend="underline"
                    >my</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">self</hi> &amp; <hi rend="underline">five</hi> other <hi
                    rend="underline">sons</hi> at home.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">When my son reaches your<lb/> city I shall endeavour to bring<lb/>
                you together &amp; I feel assured<lb/> your arguments &amp; reasoning by<lb/> word
                of mouth will have a<lb/> happier tendency than letter<lb/>
                    communicationsâ€”<persName>Mrs Moses</persName><lb/> desires her kind regards to
                you<lb/> In hopes of <hi rend="underline">soon</hi> hearing from<lb/> you I am Dr
                Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Very Resptly Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Perry Moses</persName>
            </p>
            <p>N. B. Please regard </p>
            <p>this letter as private.</p>
        </body>
